article.description: — Honor Huff's 16 points helped Chattanooga defeat Bellarmine 72-64 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Chattanooga wins 72-64 against Bellarmine
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. -- — Honor Huff's 16 points helped Chattanooga defeat Bellarmine 72-64 on Tuesday night. Huff shot 7 for 16, including 0 for 6 from beyond the arc for the Mocs (3-0). Sam Alexis added 14 points while going 6 of 9 from the field, and they also had nine rebounds. Myles Che shot 3 of 4 from the field and 7 for 8 from the line to finish with 14 points. Peter Suder led the way for the Knights (0-3) with 21 points and four steals. Bellarmine also got 19 points from Ben Johnson. In addition, Garrett Tipton finished with 11 points. Up next for Chattanooga is a Sunday matchup with Tennessee Tech at home. Bellarmine visits Bowling Green on Friday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
